Though rotund and self-containing, Solus Rex, first published in Russian in spring 1940, in the last issue (LXX) of the émigré review Sovremennīya Zapiski, Paris, is, or rather was, a chapter in a novel I never finished. The present translation, made in February 1971 by my son with my collaboration, is scrupulously faithful to the original text, including the restoration of a somewhat gamey scene that had been marked in the Sovr. Zap. by suspension points (and has put off a